        "paragraph_index": 1,
        "text": "## Which metal ion has the most different ligands studied in NIST SRD-46?\n\n**H⁺ (the proton)** tops the list with **4,081 unique ligands**, but it is not a conventional metal ion — it appears in SRD-46 because protonation equilibria (pKₐ) are recorded for virtually every ligand.\n\nAmong **true metal ions**, **Cu²⁺ (copper(II))** holds the record with **1,951 different ligands** studied.",
